1
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:38,120
[See Your Love]

2
00:00:48,410 --> 00:00:52,700
[Episode 9]

3
00:00:56,060 --> 00:00:57,130
The doctor said

4
00:00:58,660 --> 00:01:00,020
your mom will be fine.

5
00:01:08,840 --> 00:01:10,120
[Operating]

6
00:01:13,050 --> 00:01:14,600
It's not your fault.

7
00:01:16,060 --> 00:01:17,230
Go away.

8
00:01:18,200 --> 00:01:19,539
I'll stay with you.

9
00:01:34,210 --> 00:01:36,509
I haven't seen him angry for a long time.

10
00:01:38,039 --> 00:01:39,400
Seeing him angry,

11
00:01:39,690 --> 00:01:41,160
I feel so happy.

12
00:01:42,420 --> 00:01:44,020
All this time,

13
00:01:44,060 --> 00:01:46,729
he only lets us see him smile.

14
00:01:49,840 --> 00:01:51,440
What makes you upset?

15
00:01:55,700 --> 00:01:56,710
What's wrong with you?

16
00:01:57,970 --> 00:02:00,410
He'd rather hide everything

17
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:04,890
than share his negative feelings with us.

18
00:02:09,820 --> 00:02:11,150
I'm going to take a look.

19
00:02:19,110 --> 00:02:22,410
[Operating Room]

20
00:02:22,850 --> 00:02:24,090
You can't hear,

21
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:26,690
speak,

22
00:02:27,260 --> 00:02:29,060
or call an ambulance.

23
00:02:29,840 --> 00:02:31,079
If I hadn't been there,

24
00:02:31,110 --> 00:02:32,860
do you think you could've handled this?

25
00:02:36,829 --> 00:02:39,560
I thought you had already accepted the fact that you can't hear.

26
00:02:40,340 --> 00:02:41,490
But in the end?

27
00:02:43,280 --> 00:02:44,570
You were just pretending.

28
00:02:46,300 --> 00:02:47,850
You pretended that you could hear.

29
00:02:47,880 --> 00:02:49,380
You pretended that you didn't care.

30
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:51,050
You pretended that you were strong.

31
00:02:51,440 --> 00:02:52,710
Jiang Shaopeng!

32
00:02:53,700 --> 00:02:55,240
You can't hear!

33
00:02:55,260 --> 00:02:57,810
There are some things you can't do! Accept it!

34
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:06,820
[Operating Room]

35
00:03:03,220 --> 00:03:04,630
What do you want?

36
00:03:04,650 --> 00:03:06,640
Do you want me to thank you for helping me, a deaf person?

37
00:03:08,930 --> 00:03:10,100
That's not what I meant.

38
00:03:12,480 --> 00:03:14,150
How should I thank you?

39
00:03:14,150 --> 00:03:15,390
Bow?

40
00:03:15,390 --> 00:03:16,520
Kneel?

41
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:19,010
Or accept your love to return your favor?

42
00:03:19,840 --> 00:03:20,640
Shaopeng.

43
00:03:23,530 --> 00:03:28,170
Or admit that I'm a deaf person who should rely on others

44
00:03:28,170 --> 00:03:30,840
and needs others' sympathy and care?

45
00:03:32,740 --> 00:03:34,079
Jiang Shaopeng, calm down.

46
00:03:37,350 --> 00:03:40,380
Do you think I want this?

47
00:03:41,980 --> 00:03:44,680
If I hadn't got sick

48
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:46,980
or taken the antipyretic injection,

49
00:03:48,090 --> 00:03:51,720
I would have been a normal person like you.

50
00:03:51,820 --> 00:03:54,550
I would have been able to find a job.

51
00:03:56,930 --> 00:04:01,060
I would have known when my mom lost consciousness.

52
00:04:13,190 --> 00:04:15,960
Why me?

53
00:04:15,990 --> 00:04:17,660
Haven't I tried hard enough?

54
00:04:17,680 --> 00:04:20,450
Haven't I been patient enough?

55
00:04:25,730 --> 00:04:30,230
What else should I do so that I can hear again?

56
00:05:56,960 --> 00:05:57,940
Jiang Shaopeng,

57
00:05:59,080 --> 00:06:00,050
I won't apologize

58
00:06:00,050 --> 00:06:01,050
for what I just said.

59
00:06:12,890 --> 00:06:13,850
Honestly speaking,

60
00:06:15,740 --> 00:06:17,140
I'm very happy.

61
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:21,010
Knowing that there's something you care about

62
00:06:21,740 --> 00:06:23,110
and you're not as strong as you look

63
00:06:25,280 --> 00:06:26,590
makes me relieved.

64
00:06:28,620 --> 00:06:29,790
Because I'm weak.

65
00:06:43,310 --> 00:06:45,010
There's not much I can do for you.

66
00:06:46,770 --> 00:06:49,460
My only advantage is my good temper.

67
00:06:50,320 --> 00:06:51,390
I'm very patient.

68
00:06:52,110 --> 00:06:54,850
You can tell from how I've tolerated matters

69
00:06:55,080 --> 00:06:56,540
in my family all this time.

70
00:06:59,700 --> 00:07:03,630
The deaf can do everything except hearing.

71
00:07:04,770 --> 00:07:06,270
You've been trying hard.

72
00:07:07,050 --> 00:07:08,220
I should say

73
00:07:08,950 --> 00:07:10,110
you've been trying too hard

74
00:07:10,750 --> 00:07:12,850
to be strong.

75
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:15,600
But Jiang Shaopeng,

76
00:07:18,130 --> 00:07:20,590
being strong doesn't mean you can't be weak

77
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:23,150
or rely on others.

78
00:07:26,710 --> 00:07:27,660
Jiang Shaopeng,

79
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:35,540
you can try hard to be strong in front of anyone else,

80
00:07:37,450 --> 00:07:39,640
but in front of me, feel free to show your vulnerability.

81
00:07:42,500 --> 00:07:43,730
I won't laugh at you.

82
00:07:47,580 --> 00:07:48,580
Because I'm weaker.

83
00:07:51,010 --> 00:07:53,080
I'm not as good as you in doing housework.

84
00:07:54,060 --> 00:07:57,010
And I'm not as good as Cheng Fengjie in work.

85
00:08:00,580 --> 00:08:03,520
Think about me when you think you're weak.

86
00:08:04,450 --> 00:08:05,450
At least

87
00:08:05,470 --> 00:08:06,570
you're better than me.

88
00:09:05,860 --> 00:09:06,640
Where is Sean?

89
00:09:08,800 --> 00:09:10,000
I don't know.

90
00:09:12,170 --> 00:09:13,870
Uncle Yang sent me here.

91
00:09:14,060 --> 00:09:15,290
Are you sure you want to treat me like this

92
00:09:15,310 --> 00:09:16,250
for Sean?

93
00:09:19,850 --> 00:09:21,120
I really don't know.

