113
00:11:01,820 --> 00:11:06,860
[Jessica]

114
00:11:53,660 --> 00:11:54,530
Honey!

115
00:11:54,560 --> 00:11:55,430
Honey, what's wrong?

116
00:11:55,570 --> 00:11:56,360
What's wrong?

117
00:11:59,040 --> 00:11:59,960
Are you okay?

118
00:12:00,450 --> 00:12:01,270
You want to get up?

119
00:12:01,290 --> 00:12:02,190
Okay. Get up.

120
00:12:02,830 --> 00:12:04,560
Do you remember who I am?

121
00:12:04,600 --> 00:12:06,190
I'm your husband, Zhengyuan.

122
00:12:06,350 --> 00:12:07,510
Come on.

123
00:12:07,540 --> 00:12:08,930
I had an appendectomy,

124
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:10,270
not brain surgery.

125
00:12:10,480 --> 00:12:12,130
Keep your voice down.

126
00:12:12,160 --> 00:12:13,860
Acute appendicitis can be fatal too.

127
00:12:13,890 --> 00:12:14,570
I'm okay.

128
00:12:14,590 --> 00:12:15,230
Don't be nervous.

129
00:12:15,250 --> 00:12:16,050
That's good then.

130
00:12:17,030 --> 00:12:17,840
Where is Shaopeng?

131
00:12:19,880 --> 00:12:21,030
It's so noisy.

132
00:12:23,030 --> 00:12:24,150
Who's making noise?

133
00:12:49,300 --> 00:12:50,340
Hello.

134
00:12:52,580 --> 00:12:53,380
Hello.

135
00:13:07,680 --> 00:13:08,710
Boss, thank you.

136
00:13:09,190 --> 00:13:11,100
Thank you for doing us a big favor.

137
00:13:11,380 --> 00:13:12,010
Thank you.

138
00:13:12,040 --> 00:13:13,240
Uncle, don't stand on ceremony.

139
00:13:13,280 --> 00:13:14,290
Just call me Zixiang.

140
00:13:16,070 --> 00:13:17,460
Thank you, Zixiang.

141
00:13:18,290 --> 00:13:19,430
I'm going to accompany your mom first.

142
00:13:19,450 --> 00:13:21,130
Take good care of Boss.

143
00:13:21,150 --> 00:13:21,850
Zixiang.

144
00:13:22,660 --> 00:13:23,970
Come to our place when you're free

145
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:25,110
so that I can express my gratitude.

146
00:13:25,530 --> 00:13:26,010
Okay.

147
00:13:26,410 --> 00:13:27,440
Thank you, Uncle.

148
00:13:49,940 --> 00:13:50,740
Honey.

149
00:13:50,770 --> 00:13:51,600
Are you okay?

150
00:13:52,630 --> 00:13:53,960
Do you want me to take you to the toilet?

151
00:13:54,330 --> 00:13:54,990
No.

152
00:13:55,010 --> 00:13:56,810
I don't want to go to the toilet.

153
00:13:56,850 --> 00:13:57,640
Okay.

154
00:13:57,940 --> 00:13:59,320
Then I'll buy you some fruits.

155
00:13:59,940 --> 00:14:01,950
I just had an appendectomy.

156
00:14:01,970 --> 00:14:04,130
I can't eat.

157
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:07,740
Why did you faint?

158
00:14:08,490 --> 00:14:09,260
Shaopeng, come.

159
00:14:23,760 --> 00:14:25,120
I know

160
00:14:25,450 --> 00:14:26,420
you've been trying hard.

161
00:14:28,010 --> 00:14:30,520
Also, I was often worried that you might overexert yourself.

162
00:14:31,690 --> 00:14:33,270
But I've never thought

163
00:14:33,290 --> 00:14:34,640
why you did that.

164
00:14:36,090 --> 00:14:37,530
Last night,

165
00:14:37,550 --> 00:14:39,820
I heard what Zixiang told you.

166
00:14:40,520 --> 00:14:41,980
That was when I finally understood.

167
00:14:47,080 --> 00:14:48,310
You heard everything?

168
00:14:53,300 --> 00:14:54,570
What happened yesterday?

169
00:14:55,070 --> 00:14:56,370
Did I miss something?

170
00:15:01,420 --> 00:15:02,300
Honey.

171
00:15:03,900 --> 00:15:05,090
We were wrong.

172
00:15:10,240 --> 00:15:12,000
Since Shaopeng lost his hearing,

173
00:15:12,510 --> 00:15:15,040
we've become so worried about each other's feelings

174
00:15:15,330 --> 00:15:18,520
that we didn't dare to sit down and talk things through.

175
00:15:18,570 --> 00:15:19,430
In the end,

176
00:15:20,560 --> 00:15:22,330
in order to reassure us, our son

177
00:15:22,850 --> 00:15:25,450
wouldn't tell us even when he was wronged outside.

178
00:15:28,260 --> 00:15:29,820
You care about my feelings,

179
00:15:29,920 --> 00:15:31,590
so you played along with my silly antics

180
00:15:31,620 --> 00:15:32,760
and joked around.

181
00:15:33,800 --> 00:15:36,560
You kept your feelings hidden inside

182
00:15:38,700 --> 00:15:40,270
and never expressed yourself.

183
00:15:40,620 --> 00:15:42,330
And your words became fewer and fewer.

184
00:15:44,700 --> 00:15:47,180
I've never been someone who talks much.

185
00:15:48,190 --> 00:15:49,830
Why are you saying this now?

186
00:15:54,980 --> 00:15:56,920
Mom, don't think too much.

187
00:16:03,550 --> 00:16:05,410
I'm sorry.

188
00:16:05,860 --> 00:16:07,950
You lost your hearing because of me.

189
00:16:11,900 --> 00:16:15,440
That's why I've been strict with you since your childhood,

190
00:16:15,490 --> 00:16:16,660
insisting that you should learn sign language

191
00:16:16,690 --> 00:16:17,760
and lip reading.

192
00:16:17,860 --> 00:16:20,700
I even tried hard to raise money

193
00:16:21,110 --> 00:16:24,070
to send you abroad to learn how to speak.

194
00:16:30,590 --> 00:16:32,290
I focused so much on what I expected from you.

195
00:16:32,890 --> 00:16:33,700
I didn't tell you

196
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:35,500
why I did that.

197
00:16:37,050 --> 00:16:39,490
I asked you to learn so much

198
00:16:39,520 --> 00:16:43,390
because I hoped your future life could be easier

199
00:16:43,540 --> 00:16:46,100
and you wouldn't encounter so many difficulties.

200
00:16:46,250 --> 00:16:49,690
But I never meant for you to pretend that you could hear,

201
00:16:51,220 --> 00:16:53,620
just to reassure your father and me.

202
00:17:01,540 --> 00:17:03,610
I thought

203
00:17:03,610 --> 00:17:07,210
you wanted me...

204
00:17:07,950 --> 00:17:10,420
to be normal.

205
00:17:12,859 --> 00:17:14,700
What's not normal with you?

206
00:17:15,940 --> 00:17:16,900
Who said you're not normal?

207
00:17:23,569 --> 00:17:26,450
I thought...

208
00:17:26,480 --> 00:17:27,940
What does "normal" mean?

209
00:17:30,970 --> 00:17:34,320
I just hope you can accept yourself

210
00:17:34,360 --> 00:17:36,730
and be strong enough.

211
00:17:37,440 --> 00:17:39,240
But you shouldn't act tough.

212
00:17:39,980 --> 00:17:41,570
Just say it when

213
00:17:41,590 --> 00:17:43,450
you're tired or sad.

214
00:17:43,980 --> 00:17:45,480
It's okay to be tired

215
00:17:45,810 --> 00:17:47,910
or angry.

216
00:17:48,100 --> 00:17:50,950
You can act cute in front of me.

217
00:17:51,100 --> 00:17:52,770
You can rely on your dad.

218
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:55,010
You can get mad at us.

219
00:17:56,330 --> 00:17:58,970
Son, you've done well enough.

220
00:17:59,220 --> 00:18:02,600
We... We don't need you to be sensible for us.

221
00:18:03,350 --> 00:18:07,810
We need you to be happy for yourself.

222
00:18:13,150 --> 00:18:14,020
I'm sorry.

223
00:18:15,070 --> 00:18:17,350
Stop apologizing to me.

224
00:18:19,160 --> 00:18:20,580
We're family.

225
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:22,030
Don't be sorry.

226
00:18:22,290 --> 00:18:23,830
It's fine as long as we speak openly.

227
00:18:26,070 --> 00:18:27,210
You know what?

228
00:18:27,630 --> 00:18:29,020
Although you pretended to be a dead person or a ghost

229
00:18:29,060 --> 00:18:29,650
every day,

230
00:18:30,230 --> 00:18:31,560
I liked it.

231
00:18:32,230 --> 00:18:33,230
Every day after work,

232
00:18:33,260 --> 00:18:35,020
I'd wonder if you'd come up with a new idea.

233
00:18:36,780 --> 00:18:39,960
Do you understand what I'm trying to say?

234
00:18:42,470 --> 00:18:43,380
Ignore your father.

235
00:18:43,410 --> 00:18:43,910
Come.

236
00:18:44,490 --> 00:18:45,950
Let me hug you.

237
00:18:52,480 --> 00:18:53,650
Don't cry.

238
00:19:39,540 --> 00:19:41,280
The food you brought is so delicious.

239
00:19:41,300 --> 00:19:42,140
Right?

240
00:19:42,470 --> 00:19:44,780
I wanted to have midnight snacks with my fiancé.

241
00:19:44,960 --> 00:19:47,120
I waited for you all night, but you never returned.

242
00:19:47,140 --> 00:19:49,210
You know clearly someone out there wants to kill you,

243
00:19:49,390 --> 00:19:50,690
yet you still have the guts to go out.

244
00:19:50,710 --> 00:19:51,810
Do you want to die?

245
00:19:52,990 --> 00:19:54,290
I'm fine, right?

246
00:19:54,890 --> 00:19:55,720
Of course.

247
00:19:55,840 --> 00:19:57,260
If I hadn't asked Jonathan to pick you up,

248
00:19:57,280 --> 00:19:58,950
do you think you could come back unscathed?

249
00:20:00,300 --> 00:20:01,090
Pick me up?

250
00:20:03,440 --> 00:20:05,100
She knew my whereabouts?

251
00:20:05,690 --> 00:20:09,540
You have a fiancée but you said you like me.

252
00:20:09,970 --> 00:20:11,340
You looked for Jiang Shaopeng?

253
00:20:19,940 --> 00:20:21,790
This is between us.

254
00:20:21,810 --> 00:20:23,170
Leave him alone.

255
00:20:44,500 --> 00:20:47,130
The deaf can do everything except hearing.

256
00:20:48,970 --> 00:20:50,440
Only a fool would work so hard.

257
00:21:15,860 --> 00:21:17,250
I've packed spare clothes

258
00:21:17,270 --> 00:21:18,430
for Auntie.

259
00:21:18,560 --> 00:21:19,690
Where are the things she wants?

260
00:21:21,710 --> 00:21:22,290
Then...

261
00:21:22,940 --> 00:21:23,860
let's go back to the hospital.

262
00:21:28,680 --> 00:21:30,240
I've never seen this coat before.

263
00:21:32,730 --> 00:21:33,530
Whose coat is it?

264
00:21:35,090 --> 00:21:36,950
Yang Zixiang left it in the hospital.

265
00:21:36,950 --> 00:21:38,330
I brought it home when I came back last time.

266
00:21:40,230 --> 00:21:41,700
I'll meet him today.

267
00:21:41,820 --> 00:21:42,710
I'll help you give it to him.

268
00:21:45,590 --> 00:21:47,030
I'll give it to him myself.

269
00:21:49,360 --> 00:21:50,670
I'm going first.

270
00:21:50,690 --> 00:21:51,250
Okay.

271
00:22:15,300 --> 00:22:16,330
Ms. Zheng.

272
00:22:17,120 --> 00:22:18,090
I thought you came

273
00:22:18,120 --> 00:22:19,560
to help your fiancé.

274
00:22:21,380 --> 00:22:23,650
My supervision is the best help.

275
00:22:24,260 --> 00:22:26,270
You need to work even at this hour?

276
00:22:26,300 --> 00:22:27,240
Thank you for your hard work.

277
00:22:33,560 --> 00:22:34,310
What do you think?

278
00:22:34,760 --> 00:22:37,990
I estimate the base bid amount for this tender to be around 20 billion NT dollars,

279
00:22:38,170 --> 00:22:39,950
with a variation of no more than 30 million NT dollars.

280
00:22:40,610 --> 00:22:42,940
But we still need to assess the prices from other vendors.

